1
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:42,920
WEIYANG PUBLIC
SECURITY BUREAU NANSHAN BRANCH

2
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:45,160
ARCHIVE REGISTRY

3
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:49,680
Here it is. Yuanlongli, June 30th case,

4
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:50,840
C2643.

5
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:07,960
ARCHIVES ROOM

6
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:13,320
Mr. Xia, you've only been here a few days.

7
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:15,000
How are you so familiar with this place?

8
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:16,240
Only a few days?

9
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:19,240
I was already working here
before you even got here.

10
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:22,600
Later, when you were
assigned here after graduation,

11
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:24,600
I was transferred to the logistics office.

12
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:25,520
What a coincidence.

13
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:27,960
Before my dad retired,
he was in logistics too.

14
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,400
I took over his post.

15
00:02:29,480 --> 00:02:31,240
I've been filling in for your family.

16
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:32,680
Thank you so much.

17
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:36,600
If Captain Ran hadn't kept pushing
the higher-ups

18
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:39,480
for funding and gotten
this archive room built,

19
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:42,120
finding all these old files

20
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:44,400
wouldn't have been easy.

21
00:02:44,480 --> 00:02:46,920
That's right.
All the equipment here is the best.

22
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,760
Even the system
was built with upgrade ports.

23
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:50,280
It won't be outdated in a decade.

24
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,720
Back when Captain Ran was still here,

25
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:55,240
he loved spending time
in this archive room.

26
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:57,760
Sometimes when I looked up,

27
00:02:57,840 --> 00:03:01,480
I'd almost think
he was still sitting right there,

28
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,960
turning through files page by page.

29
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:32,840
These are all the files
from the June 30th case.

30
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,160
I won't keep disturbing you.

31
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,280
Want something to drink?

32
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,880
Plain water is fine. Thank you, Mr. Xia.

33
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:38,720
Alright. Go ahead with it.

34
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:43,720
LIST OF EVIDENCE

35
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:47,680
Pattia's staff badge.

36
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:48,800
MENGMENG NO.23

37
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:50,000
Black robe.

38
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:52,480
Cigarette butt.

39
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,160
Letter.

40
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,280
Herbal medicine bag.

41
00:03:58,160 --> 00:03:59,480
Wrench.

42
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,400
Photo of the trunk.

43
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,280
Blue leather heels.

44
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:11,640
Where are they?

45
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,680
Xiaohe, what's wrong?

46
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:17,800
Mr. Xia, if something was added later
to the evidence box,

47
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:19,240
could it have been missed in the records?

48
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:21,120
Absolutely impossible.

49
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:24,480
Whether evidence is stored
or someone checks it out,

50
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:26,440
it must be recorded.

51
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:29,560
Checked out?

52
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,200
PHYSICAL EVIDENCE CHECKOUT LOGBOOK

53
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:36,680
GLOVES

54
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:40,440
PHYSICAL EVIDENCE CHECKOUT FORM

55
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:42,960
YUANLONGLI JUNE 30TH
A PAIR OF BLUE LEATHER HEELS

56
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:44,960
CHECKED OUT BY: RAN FANGXU
STATUS: NOT RETURNED

57
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:51,000
CHECKED OUT BY: RAN FANGXU
STATUS: NOT RETURNED

58
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:53,400
Xiaohe?

59
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,040
Ms. Liang Juan.

60
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:58,520
Isn't the task force on break?
Why are you here?

61
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:00,400
I came to look
into the June 30th case files.

62
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,880
The June 30th case?

63
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,800
Wasn't that closed
more than ten years ago?

64
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:05,760
What's left to investigate?

65
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:06,760
I want to look

66
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:08,640
into a pair of blue leather heels
from the case.

67
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,960
Ms. Liang, do you know about that?

68
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:13,280
Blue leather heels?

69
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:17,680
Blue leather heels…

70
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,160
Captain Ran asked about them before.

71
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:38,480
Captain Ran.

72
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:40,520
Captain Ran.

73
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,400
What new theory are you working on now?

74
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:49,760
I'm thinking about everyday things,
like food and clothing.

75
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:54,480
Right, perfect timing.

76
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:56,960
In your view, a pair of red leather heels

77
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,200
or a pair of blue leather heels,

78
00:05:58,280 --> 00:05:59,640
which goes better with clothes?

79
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,840
That depends on what shade
of red and blue.

80
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:04,040
Mm.

81
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:14,760
This cucumber is good.

82
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,920
The red and this blue.

83
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,280
Which would you choose?

84
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:21,840
The red one is better.

85
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,800
Right. Blue doesn't go well with pants.

86
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:27,160
What if you wrapped blue leather

87
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,880
over red shoes?

88
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:31,000
Would you wear that?

89
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,760
Wrapped blue leather over red shoes?

90
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:43,840
Look, he really had
terrible straight-man taste.

91
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:48,960
BLUE LEATHER HEELS

92
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:52,360
Wait. I clearly remember Ran telling me

93
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:53,920
those blue leather heels were lost.

94
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,920
<i>How were they checked out?</i>

95
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,920
That signature is in
Uncle Ran's handwriting.

96
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,520
I couldn't mistake it.

97
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:01,640
<i>Maybe you weren't in good health</i>
<i>at that time.</i>

98
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:03,160
<i>He didn't want you to worry more.</i>

99
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:06,080
By the way, I ran
into Ms. Liang Juan just now.

100
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:08,600
She said in the winter of 2002,
Uncle Ran mentioned something about

101
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,400
"wrapped blue leather over red shoes".

102
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:12,600
Wrapped blue leather over red shoes?

103
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:14,640
Maybe Uncle Ran thought

104
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,880
those blue leather heels were fake.

105
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:19,600
Fake shoes?

106
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,720
True.

107
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,880
There were plenty of counterfeit
leather shoes back in the 1990s.

108
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:26,160
The fakest kind
were those cardboard shoes.

109
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:29,040
<i>You know, hard cardboard</i>
<i>covered with artificial leather.</i>

110
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:31,520
Then that explains it.

111
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:35,160
Once cardboard shoes get soaked,
the outer layer peels off.

112
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:37,000
Ran must've realized then

113
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:38,440
that those blue leather heels were fake.

114
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:40,600
But how could fake shoes

115
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:42,480
be an important clue?

116
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,360
Thank you.

117
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,400
Welcome.

118
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:25,440
Serve him a drink.

119
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:27,480
- No, thanks.
- Alright, sir.

120
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:32,080
Officer He, wasn't Mengmeng's case
solved ages ago?

121
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:33,559
Why are you investigating it again?

122
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:38,080
When Xu Meng was at Pattia,

123
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:40,799
did she wear
a pair of Double Fish high heels?

124
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:41,960
Blue in color.

125
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,840
If I remember correctly,

126
00:08:43,919 --> 00:08:45,960
the girls working at Pattia

127
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:48,120
wore uniforms custom-made by the boss

128
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,680
from head to toe.

129
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:52,360
But whether she wore them later
at the foot massage shop,

130
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,480
I wouldn't know.

131
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:57,880
In 2002,

132
00:08:57,960 --> 00:09:00,480
did Officer Ran ask you anything else?

133
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:04,920
I remember that rainy day in 1997.

134
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:06,720
FASHION BOUTIQUE

135
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:09,880
Thank you. Su Yuzhi,

136
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:12,400
wishing you booming business.

137
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:18,600
Bye.

138
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:23,960
That was the last time
I saw the handsome guy.

139
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:31,640
Mr. Ran is such a pity.

140
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:34,440
He was a nice guy.

141
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:36,360
He was gone just like that.

142
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:49,920
Hello, Ms. Lili.

143
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:54,200
Officer He,

144
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:57,000
it's been a long while.

145
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,960
I'm Lili. Don't you remember me?

146
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:08,720
I wasn't close to Mengmeng.

147
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:11,280
I don't know anything
about what happened to her.

148
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,600
CRIMINAL INVESTIGATION FILES

149
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:22,960
BLUE LEATHER HEELS WORN BY XU MENG

150
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,560
ON THE DAY SHE DISAPPEARED
WERE FOUND INSIDE WU SHANLONG'S HOME

151
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:40,840
All arranged by color.

152
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:46,080
Wu Shanlong shows signs
of obsessive behavior.

153
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:05,320
In 2002,

154
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:08,640
Officer Ran came to see me.

155
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:12,640
I remember it was very cold that day.

156
00:11:13,520 --> 00:11:15,640
- Here. Have some warm water.
- Thank you.

157
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:17,960
Here's our signature dish,
Spicy Stewed <i>Mao Xue Wang</i>.

158
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,120
Please enjoy your meal.

159
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:24,640
Officer Ran, you ordered so much food.

160
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:26,560
There are only two of us.
We can't finish all this.

161
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:27,800
You shouldn't have spent so much.

162
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:30,280
Not at all. If we can't
finish it, we can pack it up.

163
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:32,400
Thank you, Officer Ran.

164
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:35,920
You're welcome. I still need your help.

165
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:39,760
Can you try to recall

166
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:42,200
whether Xu Meng wore
a pair of blue leather heels

167
00:11:42,280 --> 00:11:44,680
when working at the foot massage shop?

168
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,600
Blue leather heels?

169
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:51,440
Yes. Yes, she did.

170
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:54,160
Those blue leather heels
were tall and eye-catching.

171
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:57,320
You know how it was

172
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:59,280
working at the foot massage shop.

173
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:01,480
Everyone dressed flashy

174
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,680
to attract customers and earn more money.

175
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:07,920
Were those shoes real
or fake cardboard shoes?

176
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:09,600
Definitely real.

177
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:12,000
Mengmeng wasn't well-off,

178
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:14,360
but she was very picky
about clothes and appearances.

179
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:16,200
She would never wear fake shoes.

180
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,720
Besides, we worked at a foot massage shop,

181
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:19,960
so our shoes often got wet.

182
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:22,960
If they were cardboard shoes,
they would've fallen apart long ago.

183
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:27,200
How could this be?

184
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:30,920
That expression.

185
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:33,920
Officer Ran had that same look
you have right now.

186
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:42,400
<i>The number you've dialed</i>
<i>is currently on another call.</i>

187
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:43,720
<i>Please try again later.</i>

188
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:47,760
<i>The number you've dialed</i>
<i>is currently on another call.</i>

189
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,160
DAD

190
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:51,880
<i>The number you've dialed</i>

191
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:53,360
<i>is currently on another call.</i>

192
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:08,240
KIDDO

193
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:09,640
- <i>Hello?</i>
- Hello?

194
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:11,240
- Who were you talking to?
- Who were you talking to?

195
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,280
- I found something.
- I found something.

196
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:15,000
- Wu Shanlong was framed.
- Wu Shanlong was framed.

197
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:46,880
Are you alright?

198
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:53,720
Dad, are you going to run away from home

199
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:56,640
- and leave the case aside?
- Who said I'm leaving the case aside?

200
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:58,160
I'm looking into it elsewhere.

201
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:03,440
Where are you going?

202
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:07,080
What exactly is going on?

203
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:09,880
Come.

204
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:13,800
Look at this.

205
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:16,360
You're observant.

206
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:19,440
The shoes on this rack
are arranged by color.

207
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:21,840
Only this pair of blue leather heels
is in the wrong place.

208
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:25,160
Whoever used fake blue leather heels
to frame Wu Shanlong

209
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:27,720
must've known his daily routine
extremely well.

210
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:30,520
They slipped in secretly while he was out.

211
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:32,800
But after all that planning,

212
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:35,120
they overlooked one thing,
Wu Shanlong's obsessive habits.

213
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:38,680
Also, I thought it through carefully.

214
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:41,840
The person who could frame Wu Shanlong

215
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:44,240
would need to meet all four conditions.

216
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:47,680
First, they held a grudge
against Xu Meng and her father

217
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:49,000
or were paid to kill them.

218
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:52,320
Second, they had to be able
to kill both of them

219
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:53,440
and dismember the bodies.

220
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:55,240
That would require
considerable physical strength…

221
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:56,160
NAME LIST

222
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:57,280
…and technical skills.

223
00:14:57,360 --> 00:15:01,720
Third, before the police
found Wu Shanlong,

224
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:03,560
they already knew he had a fetish

225
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:06,480
and also knew what kinds of things
he liked collecting.

226
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:11,200
Fourth, they knew Yuanlongli
like the back of their hand

227
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:12,920
and knew how to avoid the cameras.

228
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:13,920
At the same time,

229
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,720
they could keep track
of Wu Shanlong's movements.

230
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:20,960
I went over everyone on the list.

231
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:22,720
None of them fit.

232
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:26,920
Dad, you went in such a big circle
and ended up back at square one.

233
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:29,080
Doesn't that mean
you found nothing at all?

234
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:31,080
How is that nothing?

235
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:33,760
If we've gone back to square one,

236
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:35,640
Ran would've gone back too.

237
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:38,880
He must've hit a dead end
when he got here.

238
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:40,520
Think about it.

239
00:15:41,280 --> 00:15:43,680
Where would he investigate next?

240
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:51,720
<i>DE-PARADOXIFICATION IN CRIMINAL CASEWORK</i>

241
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:57,040
The center is right here. Yuanlongli.

242
00:15:57,120 --> 00:16:00,240
EVERY EVENT HAS A CENTER
BEYOND THE CENTER, THERE ARE RIPPLES

243
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:06,840
Should've said that earlier.

244
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:10,920
NEW YORK BLOCK

245
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,240
Mr. He. Mr. He.

246
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:21,400
Mr. He, are you a chum salmon?

247
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:24,000
What are you doing? Swimming upstream?

248
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:25,320
What are you talking about?

249
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:27,760
Isn't this building
a month away from demolition?

250
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:28,840
You know it's being torn down,

251
00:16:28,920 --> 00:16:30,560
so why is a respected officer like you

252
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:31,920
coming here to cause trouble?

253
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:33,560
I promise I won't cause trouble.

254
00:16:33,640 --> 00:16:35,160
I'm just here to relive
old times for a few days.

255
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:37,480
When demolition starts,
I won't hold anyone back.

256
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:38,440
I'll move out on time.

257
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:42,560
Mr. He. Mr. He.

258
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,240
Mr. He…

259
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:51,240
Almost there.

260
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:54,280
This is Wang Wuluan's unit.

261
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:58,160
In the whole building,
this is the only apartment left for rent.

262
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:06,720
- Are you alright?
- I'm fine.

263
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,200
You actually paid rent for this?

264
00:17:30,280 --> 00:17:31,480
There are many units here.

265
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:32,920
Couldn't you just pick one?

266
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,040
You see, you're too green.

267
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:41,840
Stop. Leave that for now.

268
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:45,720
Put the kettle on, make tea,
and wait for visitors.

269
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,160
This run-down place, jeez.

270
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:03,840
Coming.

271
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:09,360
Officer He.

272
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,440
- Officer He.
- Come on in.

273
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:12,680
Officer He.

274
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,600
- Officer He, you moved in.
- It's messy.

275
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:17,200
- Come in.
- Hello, Officer He.

276
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:19,480
There's no need to hold back
in Officer He's place.

277
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:24,960
Everyone, let's welcome Officer He
to his new home.

278
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:27,640
Welcome!

279
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:30,720
Officer He. Officer He.
You came at the right time.

280
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:33,280
It's great. We have a capable man
on our side now.

281
00:18:33,360 --> 00:18:35,280
Exactly. A capable helper.

282
00:18:36,560 --> 00:18:38,680
I came here with a mission.

283
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:42,280
I need you and everyone
to help me ask around.

284
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:44,960
Everything about Officer Ran

285
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:47,280
in Yuanlongli during the winter of 2002.

286
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:50,160
Who he met. What he did. What he said.

287
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:52,040
I want all of it.

288
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:55,280
Don't worry. You can count on us.

289
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:56,880
- Right.
- No problem.

290
00:18:56,960 --> 00:18:58,160
Of course.

291
00:18:58,240 --> 00:19:01,000
Looks like not everyone came today.

292
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:03,080
I suggest we create a group chat.

293
00:19:03,160 --> 00:19:04,000
- Sure.
- Right.

294
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:06,920
If anyone hears anything,
post it in the group.

295
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,560
Right.

296
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:10,440
Great idea!

297
00:19:10,520 --> 00:19:12,840
- Right.
- Good idea.

298
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:15,560
Scan the code.

299
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:16,600
HE YUANHANG

300
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:18,000
DAD, DON'T LET THEM FOOL YOU
ONCE YOU'RE IN, IT'S HARD TO BACK OUT

301
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:28,280
- Are you in?
- Yes.

302
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:30,160
- All in?
- Yes.

303
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:34,320
I only notified a few of you.
Who else is coming?

304
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:35,800
- Isn't this everyone?
- Yeah.

305
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:36,800
No one else.

306
00:19:44,880 --> 00:19:45,720
Officer He,

307
00:19:46,480 --> 00:19:49,440
this building is run-down and creepy.

308
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:52,840
Moving in here is bad for your health.

309
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:55,720
What if your situation relapses?

310
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:57,440
You're not my son.

311
00:19:57,520 --> 00:19:59,320
- You don't need to worry about my health.
- He Yuanhang,

312
00:20:00,080 --> 00:20:02,560
you're not a police officer now,
and you're not an owner here either.

313
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:05,600
Stop causing trouble
for the Redevelopment Bureau.

314
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:06,520
Jeez.

315
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:10,320
Open your eyes wide and look carefully.

316
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,160
LEASE AGREEMENT

317
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:14,640
There's a signature and a stamp.

318
00:20:15,320 --> 00:20:16,800
I'm a legal tenant.

319
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:18,840
Who's causing trouble now?

320
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,960
Money-grubber, you played tricks
on our demolition agreement.

321
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:25,280
You promised compensation
and didn't deliver.

322
00:20:25,360 --> 00:20:28,800
If you want to tear down my home,
that'll be at least ten million.

323
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:30,840
Not one single dime less.

324
00:20:30,920 --> 00:20:32,320
Ten million!

325
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:33,840
Ten million!

326
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:35,480
Ten million!

327
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:37,360
Ten million!

328
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:38,680
Ten million!

329
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,040
- We did it!
- We won!

330
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:43,000
Drink some tea.

331
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:44,360
Drink tea.

332
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:45,680
Carry on.

333
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:47,280
Is the water ready?

334
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:51,440
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

335
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:55,680
- Start the chant.
- Let's go.

336
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:57,760
As long as we still have our homes,

337
00:20:57,840 --> 00:20:59,560
we can wait!

338
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:01,400
Bad terms?

339
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:03,520
We're not selling!

340
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,480
As long as we still have our homes,

341
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,080
we can wait!

342
00:21:09,480 --> 00:21:13,080
Dad, can't you clean up tomorrow?

343
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:16,160
The real work hasn't even started.

344
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:18,000
Go home and sleep
after everything is done.

345
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:21,640
Are you sure you don't need me here?

346
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:23,200
We're partners this time.

347
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:25,000
I manage inside. You take the outside.

348
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:26,840
We'll block them from both sides.

349
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:28,800
There's no way we can't crack this case.

350
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:31,120
Get up. Get to work.

351
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:38,240
Open the windows wider.

352
00:21:47,880 --> 00:21:51,520
FAKE BLUE LEATHER HEELS

353
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:04,920
Dad, even the task force
can't match this setup.

354
00:22:06,120 --> 00:22:09,000
Before troops move, supplies go first.

355
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:13,360
Team Leader He, what are your next orders?

356
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:15,600
I'm not a team leader.

357
00:22:16,120 --> 00:22:18,160
The team leader is Ran.

358
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:19,560
What we need to do now

359
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:22,080
is guess what his next move would be.

360
00:22:24,360 --> 00:22:25,920
If I were him,

361
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:30,640
once I got to Yuanlongli,
I'd first use Tremaux's algorithm.

362
00:22:33,280 --> 00:22:35,040
I'll do the building canvass.

363
00:22:35,120 --> 00:22:38,400
Tomorrow, I'll go through every place
in this building

364
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:39,880
connected to the June 30th case.

365
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:41,840
I'll go to the property management

366
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:44,760
and check the resident
and tenant list from 2002.

367
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:47,040
And ask whether Uncle Ran
visited any of them back then.

368
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:49,920
Good. That's the plan.

369
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:52,200
Go home now. Rest up early.

370
00:23:01,240 --> 00:23:02,680
How come you're older now,

371
00:23:02,760 --> 00:23:04,040
but still full of energy?

372
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:08,040
I have more than enough strength
to handle ten men alone.

373
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:11,080
Remember to take
your blood pressure medicine.

374
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:13,120
The wind gets strong at night.
Remember to close the windows.

375
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:16,080
You're so naggy. Go on.

376
00:24:44,320 --> 00:24:47,000
I'm leaving, sir.

377
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:50,120
Ran,

378
00:24:52,560 --> 00:24:54,520
you always saw me as your mentor.

379
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:59,440
But you're the one who taught me.

380
00:25:28,280 --> 00:25:29,640
2002 YUANLONGLI RESIDENTIAL
COMPLEX OWNER/TENANT REGISTRATION FORM

381
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:50,320
My goodness! Run!

382
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:51,440
Hey!

383
00:27:38,440 --> 00:27:41,520
Du Mingliang, can I count you as a human?

384
00:27:41,600 --> 00:27:44,200
Playing games all day long.

385
00:27:44,280 --> 00:27:46,440
I'd rather have given birth
to a bun than you.

386
00:28:36,040 --> 00:28:37,400
Mr. He. Bollard!

387
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:45,120
Mr. He, I heard you moved in.

388
00:28:46,760 --> 00:28:49,360
Many people moved out.
When are you planning to move?

389
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:50,600
I'm not moving.

390
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:52,600
I signed a long-term lease.

391
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:54,440
I spent a lot of money
renovating the shop.

392
00:28:55,040 --> 00:28:56,520
That money-grubber

393
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:58,640
tries to tear down illegally
and not pay me a dime.

394
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:01,320
That's ridiculous.
I'm fighting him to the end.

395
00:29:02,760 --> 00:29:03,760
Join this group chat.

396
00:29:05,360 --> 00:29:07,520
Holdouts Group? What's this for?

397
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:08,480
We're all on the same side.

398
00:29:08,560 --> 00:29:10,240
Oh, so you made a group there.

399
00:29:11,720 --> 00:29:14,000
Mr. He, why did you move in
at a time like this?

400
00:29:14,080 --> 00:29:15,160
Working on a case?

401
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:17,040
Let me ask you this.

402
00:29:17,120 --> 00:29:19,280
In the winter of 2002,

403
00:29:19,360 --> 00:29:20,920
did you see Officer Ran?

404
00:29:25,440 --> 00:29:27,560
I wasn't supposed to tell you.

405
00:29:28,280 --> 00:29:30,720
But now I guess I can.

406
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:32,720
Go on.

407
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:35,760
Come out here!

408
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:38,080
If you don't give me back the mouse,

409
00:29:38,160 --> 00:29:39,560
I'll go on a hunger strike for a month!

410
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:41,040
Oh, I'm so scared of you.

411
00:29:41,120 --> 00:29:42,760
A whole month of hunger strike?

412
00:29:44,360 --> 00:29:46,280
- Madam.
- Officer Ran,

413
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:47,960
perfect timing.

414
00:29:48,040 --> 00:29:50,800
Help me drag this brat out.

415
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:53,720
You won't let me be a cybercafe manager
or open a cybercafé.

416
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:55,840
Then I'll open the window
and live on air then.

417
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:57,160
Go ahead.

418
00:29:57,240 --> 00:29:58,760
No one's scared of you.

419
00:30:03,240 --> 00:30:05,200
Du Mingliang, listen to me.

420
00:30:05,280 --> 00:30:07,760
Whether to be a manager
or open a cybercafé,

421
00:30:07,840 --> 00:30:09,360
you first need technical skills.

422
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:11,320
There are courses online now.

423
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:14,200
You can sign up for computer science
and study at home.

424
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:16,200
Where did you see that?

425
00:30:16,800 --> 00:30:19,160
I can register it for you.
But first, you need to eat.

426
00:30:20,960 --> 00:30:23,080
Come out first.

427
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:24,600
Eat your dinner.

428
00:30:30,120 --> 00:30:31,520
Jeez.

429
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:35,440
Madam, let me ask you something.

430
00:30:35,520 --> 00:30:39,160
Did you see any strangers
go into No. 1703 this summer?

431
00:30:39,240 --> 00:30:41,240
You mean the Wu family?

432
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:44,880
Their door is always shut.

433
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:46,800
I only saw it open once.

434
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:49,280
At the time,
the whole place was full of police.

435
00:30:58,560 --> 00:31:02,560
Right, have you seen
double-layer leather shoes?

436
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:04,240
What is that?

437
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:07,560
Shoes with one layer inside
and another layer wrapped outside.

438
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:09,040
Counterfeit designer shoes.

439
00:31:11,120 --> 00:31:12,720
I have seen

440
00:31:12,800 --> 00:31:14,440
cardboard shoes before.

441
00:31:14,520 --> 00:31:16,480
Whoever made those
double-layer leather shoes

442
00:31:17,400 --> 00:31:19,880
must've had something wrong up top.

443
00:31:19,960 --> 00:31:21,440
Why wrap another layer

444
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:23,520
over a perfectly good pair of shoes?

445
00:31:24,360 --> 00:31:25,960
I have seen that kind of shoes.

446
00:31:26,040 --> 00:31:27,640
The person making shoes like that

447
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:29,880
must be a very experienced craftsman.

448
00:31:30,680 --> 00:31:32,720
Think about it. Two layers of leather

449
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:35,760
and still made to look
exactly like the real thing.

450
00:31:35,840 --> 00:31:38,360
You know, that's not easy.

451
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:39,880
Do you know any craftsmen like this?

452
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:42,120
No.

453
00:31:43,080 --> 00:31:46,320
But you can ask those who sell fake shoes.

454
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:48,440
They would definitely know.

455
00:31:51,760 --> 00:31:53,600
<i>Then Officer Ran left.</i>

456
00:31:54,560 --> 00:31:56,840
Before leaving,
he specifically told me this.

457
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:58,280
If I ran into you,

458
00:31:58,360 --> 00:32:00,920
I must not tell you that he had come by

459
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:03,320
or what questions he asked.

460
00:32:04,040 --> 00:32:06,440
Mr. He, aren't you his mentor?

461
00:32:06,520 --> 00:32:07,720
Why would he hide it from you?

462
00:32:09,120 --> 00:32:10,320
Double-layer leather shoes.

463
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:13,520
Fake shoe sellers.

464
00:32:16,080 --> 00:32:18,840
Right. Guess what I saw
at the night market.

465
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:21,760
Those same blue leather heels
the missing woman wore

466
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:23,080
are called Double Fish.

467
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:25,120
Seems like a name brand. Pretty expensive.

468
00:32:26,760 --> 00:32:29,920
So why didn't you clear your head too?

469
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:33,280
You think branded shoes sold
at the night market are real?

470
00:32:37,880 --> 00:32:40,440
Mr. He. You're leaving?

471
00:32:40,520 --> 00:32:42,600
Put the property list aside for now.

472
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:44,040
Go to the Commerce Bureau.

473
00:32:44,120 --> 00:32:45,880
Check the list of shoe and hat vendors

474
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:48,680
at the Riverside Night Market in 1997.

475
00:32:49,240 --> 00:32:50,680
Contact them one by one.

476
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:53,240
Ask whether Ran went
looking for them back then.

477
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:54,760
<i>All vendors?</i>

478
00:32:54,840 --> 00:32:56,000
Every single one.

479
00:32:56,080 --> 00:32:57,760
<i>That's a huge workload.</i>

480
00:32:57,840 --> 00:32:58,840
Hurry up.

481
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:01,320
Give us a straight answer.

482
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:03,920
Can the relocation payout
still be negotiated or not?

483
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:07,000
Otherwise, we old folks here
would rather die

484
00:33:07,080 --> 00:33:09,400
right here in Yuanlongli.

485
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:11,640
Right! We'll die right here in Yuanlongli!

486
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:13,080
As long as we still have our homes,

487
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:15,120
we can wait!

488
00:33:15,200 --> 00:33:16,840
Bad terms?

489
00:33:16,920 --> 00:33:18,280
We're not selling!

490
00:33:18,360 --> 00:33:20,280
Everyone, please calm down.

491
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:22,240
Kick up all the fuss you want.

492
00:33:22,320 --> 00:33:24,560
Not one extra dime
will be added to the compensation.

493
00:33:24,640 --> 00:33:26,200
- You!
- When the time comes,

494
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:28,320
I'll bring the demolition crew
and bury explosives here.

495
00:33:28,400 --> 00:33:29,320
Whoever won't leave,

496
00:33:29,400 --> 00:33:31,320
I'll bury explosives at their front door.

497
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:33,800
- How can you say this?
- Qian, you bastard!

498
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:34,880
If you dare do that,

499
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:36,560
I'll drag you down with me!

500
00:33:36,640 --> 00:33:38,640
Exactly! Go down together!

501
00:33:39,360 --> 00:33:40,960
- Alright, everyone.
- Go down together!

502
00:33:41,040 --> 00:33:42,840
Will you stop already?

503
00:33:42,920 --> 00:33:45,680
I'm the project manager here.
You just need to cooperate.

504
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:46,600
We're all old neighbors.

505
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:48,320
Is there any point in bluffing
and tricking them like this?

506
00:33:49,160 --> 00:33:50,000
I cooperate with you?

507
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:53,880
Everyone from Yuanlongli knows
what kind of person you used to be.

508
00:33:59,360 --> 00:34:02,400
Some people have dirty minds.

509
00:34:02,480 --> 00:34:03,640
So everything they see looks dirty.

510
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:06,840
Officer He,

511
00:34:07,560 --> 00:34:09,719
this is a matter for the owners.

512
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:11,679
You're just a tenant.
You don't get a share of the money, right?

513
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:16,880
Qian, you're not young anymore.

514
00:34:17,679 --> 00:34:19,560
You should really do something
about your bad breath.

515
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:22,280
Well said!

516
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:24,239
Exactly right!

517
00:34:26,760 --> 00:34:27,880
Let me make this clear.

518
00:34:27,960 --> 00:34:31,560
Everyone should raise demands
reasonably and legally.

519
00:34:31,639 --> 00:34:33,199
Don't act without order.

520
00:34:33,880 --> 00:34:36,159
Qiao is only doing her job.

521
00:34:36,239 --> 00:34:37,760
But the way she handles things

522
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:39,679
is nothing like certain people.

523
00:34:40,280 --> 00:34:42,719
So don't lash out at everybody.

524
00:34:42,800 --> 00:34:44,040
Can you do that?

525
00:34:49,400 --> 00:34:52,400
Can't do it? Then I'm leaving
the group chat right now.

526
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:54,600
- Please!
- No!

527
00:34:54,679 --> 00:34:56,520
- Officer He!
- Officer He,

528
00:34:57,280 --> 00:34:59,680
what you just said
was deeply philosophical.

529
00:35:00,400 --> 00:35:03,400
From now on, we won't
make things hard for Miss Qiao.

530
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:04,320
- We won't do that.
- That's right.

531
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:05,200
We won't do that to her.

532
00:35:05,280 --> 00:35:06,400
No.

533
00:35:07,400 --> 00:35:09,880
We'll go after the one
who's really to blame.

534
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:11,280
- That's right.
- We'll go after the one

535
00:35:11,360 --> 00:35:12,320
who's really to blame.

536
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:14,440
As long as we still have our homes,

537
00:35:14,520 --> 00:35:16,280
we can wait!

538
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:18,200
Bad terms?

539
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:20,480
As long as we still have our homes…

540
00:35:20,560 --> 00:35:22,680
As long as we still have our homes,

541
00:35:22,760 --> 00:35:24,720
we can wait!

542
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:26,600
Bad terms?

543
00:35:26,680 --> 00:35:28,680
We're not selling!

544
00:35:28,760 --> 00:35:30,880
Qiao, don't worry.

545
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:33,320
As long as I'm here,
nothing will go wrong.

546
00:35:34,080 --> 00:35:35,640
Thank you, Mr. He.

547
00:35:36,560 --> 00:35:39,920
There's something I'd like
to ask for your help with.

548
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:42,680
Can you think of a way

549
00:35:42,760 --> 00:35:45,680
to delay the demolition deadline
a little longer?

550
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:47,400
Mr. He,

551
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:51,000
why did you get involved in this too?

552
00:35:51,080 --> 00:35:53,080
Ran left with regret.

553
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:57,400
I have to stay in Yuanlongli for a while

554
00:35:57,480 --> 00:36:00,120
and help him make up for it
and fulfill his wish.

555
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:09,200
Alright.

556
00:36:10,120 --> 00:36:11,360
I'll do my best to help.

557
00:36:26,480 --> 00:36:28,440
Mister, please do me a favor.

558
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:30,040
I'll remember you for life.

559
00:36:41,560 --> 00:36:43,600
TO LET

560
00:36:53,240 --> 00:36:54,200
CALL

561
00:36:57,520 --> 00:36:58,520
<i>Hello?</i>

562
00:36:58,600 --> 00:36:59,880
Hello?

563
00:36:59,960 --> 00:37:02,280
I'd like to ask about the shop
you had for rent.

564
00:37:02,360 --> 00:37:05,040
Did you rent it to a woman
who sold shoes in 1997?

565
00:37:05,680 --> 00:37:07,840
<i>1997? I can't remember.</i>

566
00:37:07,920 --> 00:37:09,880
She had short hair and was very outgoing.

567
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:11,640
Whenever someone passed her shop,

568
00:37:11,720 --> 00:37:13,520
she'd pull them over to look at her shoes.

569
00:37:14,120 --> 00:37:15,560
And she would say things like,

570
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:18,200
"Please do me a favor, mister.

571
00:37:18,280 --> 00:37:20,760
I'll remember you for life."

572
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:23,880
<i>Now I remember. That must be Liu Guifang.</i>

573
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:25,600
<i>She couldn't afford the rent anymore.</i>

574
00:37:25,680 --> 00:37:27,120
<i>She insisted on using</i>
<i>her stock to cover it.</i>

575
00:37:27,200 --> 00:37:28,520
<i>Those were the exact words she used.</i>

576
00:37:29,120 --> 00:37:31,160
<i>I felt soft-hearted at the time,</i>
<i>so I let it slide.</i>

577
00:37:31,240 --> 00:37:32,440
Where did she go after that?

578
00:37:52,560 --> 00:37:55,000
I called you.
Why was your phone off again?

579
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:57,480
Do you know how many vendors

580
00:37:57,560 --> 00:37:58,880
there were at
Riverside Night Market in 1997?

581
00:37:59,480 --> 00:38:00,400
More than 500.

582
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:02,200
Even if I had three phones,
they would all be dead by now.

583
00:38:03,760 --> 00:38:04,760
Did you find anything?

584
00:38:06,600 --> 00:38:11,120
Uncle Ran contacted
someone named Liu Guifang.

585
00:38:12,120 --> 00:38:13,080
Here.

586
00:38:13,160 --> 00:38:14,000
LIU GUIFANG

587
00:38:43,920 --> 00:38:45,840
MAHJONG AND TEA,WELCOME INSIDE

588
00:38:48,240 --> 00:38:50,960
<i>I heard Liu Guifang got together</i>
<i>with the owner of a mahjong parlor.</i>

589
00:38:51,040 --> 00:38:52,400
<i>He received a hefty demolition payout</i>

590
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:54,000
<i>from several houses</i>
<i>he owned in the village.</i>

591
00:38:54,080 --> 00:38:55,120
<i>He got rich long ago.</i>

592
00:39:12,240 --> 00:39:14,640
Come on. Be generous.

593
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:16,600
Just do me a favor, mister.

594
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:18,160
I'll remember you for life.

595
00:39:22,480 --> 00:39:24,880
Alright. I'm hanging up now, Yao.

596
00:39:26,320 --> 00:39:28,520
- Excuse me.
- Playing mahjong?

597
00:39:28,600 --> 00:39:30,200
Five years ago,
at the Riverside Night Market,

598
00:39:30,280 --> 00:39:32,000
you sold me a pair of fake leather shoes.

599
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:33,080
They were cardboard shoes.

600
00:39:33,160 --> 00:39:34,840
What? Five years ago?

601
00:39:39,080 --> 00:39:40,080
It's been five years.

602
00:39:40,680 --> 00:39:43,800
Mister, you really hold grudges.

603
00:39:45,640 --> 00:39:47,440
I definitely don't remember you.

604
00:39:47,520 --> 00:39:49,440
But back then, I did sell fake shoes.

605
00:39:50,520 --> 00:39:53,200
How about this?
I'll pay you ten times the price.

606
00:39:53,280 --> 00:39:54,520
Is that okay?

607
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:04,880
You sold Double Fish back then.

608
00:40:04,960 --> 00:40:05,960
They came in several colors.

609
00:40:06,040 --> 00:40:07,080
Do you know who in Weiyang

610
00:40:07,160 --> 00:40:09,000
could make this kind
of double-layer leather heels?

611
00:40:09,080 --> 00:40:10,560
Double-layer leather heels?

612
00:40:11,160 --> 00:40:12,480
Let me see.

613
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:15,520
Don't open it.

614
00:40:18,360 --> 00:40:20,520
Double-layer leather heels…
That's pretty unusual.

615
00:40:21,120 --> 00:40:23,440
Judging from the finish and workmanship,

616
00:40:23,520 --> 00:40:26,120
that should be Mr. Lu
from Pingzhao County.

617
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:28,000
Bet you didn't know.

618
00:40:28,080 --> 00:40:30,720
Mr. Lu was a master
of fake shoes in Weiyang.

619
00:40:30,800 --> 00:40:32,880
The shoes he made
could pass for the real thing.

620
00:40:34,120 --> 00:40:35,520
Pingzhao County.

621
00:40:38,680 --> 00:40:39,840
MAP

622
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:45,040
PINGZHAO COUNTY

623
00:40:57,120 --> 00:41:00,400
PINGZHAO COUNTY

624
00:41:01,160 --> 00:41:02,400
It's been 13 years.

625
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:05,840
No idea whether Mr. Lu is still around.

626
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:09,560
NO. 6, LU VILLAGE, BEISHI TOWN
PINGZHAO COUNTY, WEIYANG CITY

627
00:41:09,640 --> 00:41:12,360
Uncle Ran probably
has taken this road too.

628
00:41:15,560 --> 00:41:17,360
We've picked the trail back up at last.
